@jgao54 I have Airflow deploying against the 1.10 branch and started seeing crashes this morning due to this PR:

`May 10 13:20:27 airflow-sandbox-i-0c242b6d27a89dc1c.stg.int.dynoquant.com airflow_web-stderr.log: airflow.exceptions.AirflowConfigException: section/key [webserver/navbar_color] not found in config`

Not sure if there's a further PR pending, but presumably this setting should have a default or a config file entry.

@mistercrunch 
NullPool does work, but a regression caused the connection pool settings to use QueuePool instead. 
Thanks for taking a look!

@saguziel 
with about 9.5k - 11k running tasks, DBU CPU wildly varied from 6% - 14% without my change.
With my change, as DB connections decreased from 20k to less than 200, DB CPU increased from 8% to 10%, which is reasonable given any volatility already present, so difficult to even tell if due to my changes.
